From 38128c04cfba5be5dcc619678043990fce383108 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ganesh Kariganuru Mahabalesh <gkarigan@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 22 Sep 2025 14:50:38 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:DP:wifi:ath12k:Fix crash in ath12k_dp_cc_cleanup due
 to missing ar in skb_cb

In the Tx fast path, skb_cb->u.ar was not being initialized, leading to a
NULL ar during ath12k_dp_cc_cleanup.
This caused a crash when atomic_dec_and_test(&ar->dp.num_tx_pending) was
invoked.
Fix this by explicitly setting ar in the skb_cb in Tx fast path in
ath12k_wifi7_mac_op_tx() to ensure ar is available during cleanup.

Patch-Dependency:
	0374-QSDK-DP-wifi-ath12k-Remove-tx_desc_used_list-from-Tx.patch
Fixes:
	I8ed64ec1ed8(QSDK: DP wifi: ath12k: Tx KPI Optimizations)

Signed-off-by: Ganesh Kariganuru Mahabalesh <gkarigan@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/hw.c |    1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/hw.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/wifi7/hw.c
@@ -1371,6 +1371,7 @@ static void ath12k_wifi7_mac_op_tx(struc
 		}
 
 		ar = arvif->ar;
+		skb_cb->u.ar = ar;
 
 		dp_pdev = ath12k_dp_to_dp_pdev(ar->ab->dp, ar->pdev_idx);
 		if (unlikely(!dp_pdev)) {
